    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "## Problem\n\nIf a prompt buffer is renamed with `:file`, then `:edit!` in the buffer clears its contents. That doesn't seem useful.\n\n```\n:set buftype=prompt\n:file foo\niabc<cr> # enter some text\n:set nomodified\n:edit\n```\n\nIt's common for plugins to (1) rename a prompt buffer, and (2) set 'nomodified', because seeing \"unsaved changes\" warnings in prompt buffers is generally unwelcome and irrelevant for prompt applications.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\n`:edit` in a prompt-buffer should only trigger an event. It's trivial for plugins to clear the buffer if they want, whereas preserving its contents requires more logic.",
